---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', text: 'Quick Verdict', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Side-by-Side Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'cigna', text: 'Cigna Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'bupa', text: 'Bupa Global', level: 2 },
  { id: 'aetna', text: 'Aetna International', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'regional-details', text: 'Southeast Asia Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'best-for', text: 'Which Is Best For You?', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'FAQs', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { href: '/countries/thailand/insurance', text: 'Thailand Insurance' },
  { href: '/insurance-for/digital-nomads', text: 'Digital Nomad Insurance' },
  { href: '/providers/cigna-global', text: 'Cigna Global Review' },
  { href: '/providers/bupa-global', text: 'Bupa Global Review' },
  { href: '/providers/aetna-international', text: 'Aetna International Review' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
];

const mainComparisonRows = [
  { feature: 'Thailand Network', cigna: 'Excellent (200+)', bupa: 'Very Good (150+)', aetna: 'Good (100+)' },
  { feature: 'Singapore Network', cigna: 'Excellent', bupa: 'Excellent', aetna: 'Very Good' },
  { feature: 'Vietnam Network', cigna: 'Good (urban)', bupa: 'Limited', aetna: 'Growing' },
  { feature: 'Direct Billing', cigna: 'Best in region', bupa: 'Major hospitals', aetna: 'Major cities' },
  { feature: 'Coverage Limit', cigna: 'Unlimited', bupa: 'Unlimited', aetna: 'Up to $5M' },
  { feature: 'Tropical Disease', cigna: 'Full coverage', bupa: 'Full coverage', aetna: 'Full coverage' },
  { feature: 'Evacuation', cigna: 'Included', bupa: 'Included', aetna: 'Included' },
  { feature: 'Regional Pricing', cigna: 'Mid-range', bupa: 'Premium', aetna: 'Most affordable' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'Bupa Global' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Individual (35)', cigna: '$280-380/mo', bupa: '$320-450/mo', aetna: '$220-320/mo' },
  { profile: 'Individual (50)', cigna: '$450-620/mo', bupa: '$520-720/mo', aetna: '$380-520/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple (35/35)', cigna: '$530-720/mo', bupa: '$610-850/mo', aetna: '$420-600/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family (2+2)', cigna: '$800-1,100/mo', bupa: '$920-1,280/mo', aetna: '$650-900/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna vs Bupa vs Aetna for Southeast Asia | 2025 Comparison"
  description="Compare Cigna Global, Bupa Global, and Aetna International for expats in Southeast Asia. Expert analysis covering Thailand, Singapore, Vietnam, Indonesia, and Malaysia."
  headline="Cigna vs Bupa vs Aetna: Best Insurance for Southeast Asia"
  subheadline="Complete comparison for expats in Thailand, Singapore, Vietnam, Indonesia, Malaysia, and the Philippines—covering networks, tropical coverage, and regional pricing."
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes"
  ctaButtonHref="/get-quotes"
>
  <section id="quick-verdict" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Quick Verdict</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary-800 mb-2">Cigna Global</h3>
        <p class="text-primary-700 mb-3">Best Overall for SEA</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">Largest direct billing network across Thailand, Singapore, and Vietnam. Best balance of coverage, network, and price for the region.</p>
        <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-primary-700 transition text-sm" style="color: white !important;">Learn More</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border border-purple-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-purple-800 mb-2">Bupa Global</h3>
        <p class="text-purple-700 mb-3">Best Premium Hospitals</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">Access to top-tier hospitals like Bumrungrad and Mount Elizabeth. Premium service for those wanting the best facilities.</p>
        <a href="/providers/bupa-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-purple-700 transition text-sm" style="color: white !important;">Learn More</a>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Aetna International</h3>
        <p class="text-green-700 mb-3">Best Value</p>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm mb-4">Most affordable premium coverage for the region. Good networks in major cities at 20-30% lower cost than competitors.</p>
        <a href="/providers/aetna-international" class="inline-block bg-green-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded hover:bg-green-700 transition text-sm" style="color: white !important;">Learn More</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="comparison-table" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </section>

  <section id="cigna" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Cigna Global</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
      <span class="bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Best Network</span>
      <span class="bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Direct Billing</span>
      <span class="bg-primary-100 text-primary-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Regional Expertise</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Cigna Global has the strongest overall network in Southeast Asia. In Thailand alone, they have direct billing agreements with over 200 hospitals and clinics—from Bangkok's premium facilities to provincial hospitals in Chiang Mai, Phuket, and beyond. This regional depth is unmatched.</p>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Their Singapore network includes all major private hospitals, and they've been expanding rapidly in Vietnam and Indonesia. The unlimited coverage means no concerns about Singapore's expensive healthcare. Regional customer service teams understand local healthcare systems and can guide you effectively.</p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Regional Strengths</h4>
        <ul class="text-green-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Largest Thailand network (200+)</li>
          <li>• Excellent Singapore coverage</li>
          <li>• Growing Vietnam presence</li>
          <li>• Direct billing widely available</li>
          <li>• Regional support teams</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="text-amber-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Mid-range pricing (not cheapest)</li>
          <li>• Some rural areas limited</li>
          <li>• Cambodia/Myanmar sparse</li>
          <li>• Prior authorization required sometimes</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="/providers/cigna-global" class="inline-block bg-primary-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
  </section>

  <section id="bupa" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Bupa Global</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
      <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Premium Facilities</span>
      <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Singapore Focus</span>
      <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Service Quality</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Bupa Global focuses on premium hospital access in Southeast Asia. Their network includes prestigious facilities like Bumrungrad (Bangkok), Mount Elizabeth (Singapore), and Raffles Hospital. If you want access to the region's best hospitals with VIP service, Bupa delivers.</p>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Their Singapore network is particularly strong—important given the city-state's position as a medical hub. Care coordination helps navigate complex treatments across different countries. The trade-off is higher premiums and a somewhat smaller overall network compared to Cigna.</p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Regional Strengths</h4>
        <ul class="text-green-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Top-tier hospital partnerships</li>
          <li>• Excellent Singapore network</li>
          <li>• Premium Bangkok facilities</li>
          <li>• Care coordination service</li>
          <li>• VIP treatment access</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="text-amber-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• Highest premiums</li>
          <li>• Smaller network outside cities</li>
          <li>• Vietnam coverage limited</li>
          <li>• Less presence in Philippines</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="/providers/bupa-global" class="inline-block bg-purple-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-purple-700 transition font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Bupa Quote</a>
  </section>

  <section id="aetna" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Aetna International</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-4">
      <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Best Value</span>
      <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Good Networks</span>
      <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">US Brand</span>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Aetna International offers the best value for Southeast Asia coverage. Their premiums run 20-30% lower than Cigna and Bupa while still providing solid coverage at quality hospitals. For cost-conscious expats, Aetna delivers quality healthcare access without premium pricing.</p>

    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Networks cover major cities well—Bangkok, Singapore, Kuala Lumpur, and Ho Chi Minh City all have good direct billing options. The trade-off is less depth outside urban centers and the $5M limit (though sufficient for virtually all scenarios in the region). They've been growing their Asia presence significantly.</p>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Regional Strengths</h4>
        <ul class="text-green-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• 20-30% lower premiums</li>
          <li>• Good major city networks</li>
          <li>• Growing Vietnam presence</li>
          <li>• Strong Malaysia coverage</li>
          <li>• Familiar US brand</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4">
        <h4 class="font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2">Considerations</h4>
        <ul class="text-amber-700 text-sm space-y-1">
          <li>• $5M limit (vs unlimited)</li>
          <li>• Smaller overall network</li>
          <li>• Limited rural coverage</li>
          <li>• Fewer premium hospital ties</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="/providers/aetna-international" class="inline-block bg-green-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-green-700 transition font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Aetna Quote</a>
  </section>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Southeast Asia Coverage"
    description="Get quotes optimized for your Southeast Asian destination."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/get-quotes"
  />

  <section id="pricing" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Pricing Comparison</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">Regional pricing for Southeast Asia (excluding Singapore):</p>
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-4">*Singapore-only coverage costs 30-50% more due to high healthcare costs. Prices for comprehensive inpatient + outpatient coverage.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="regional-details" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Southeast Asia Details</h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Country-by-Country</h3>
        <ul class="text-neutral-700 text-sm space-y-2">
          <li>• <strong>Thailand:</strong> All three excellent; Cigna leads</li>
          <li>• <strong>Singapore:</strong> All three excellent; Bupa premium focus</li>
          <li>• <strong>Vietnam:</strong> Cigna best; Aetna growing; Bupa limited</li>
          <li>• <strong>Indonesia:</strong> Cigna and Aetna good; Jakarta focused</li>
          <li>• <strong>Malaysia:</strong> All three solid; KL/Penang</li>
          <li>• <strong>Philippines:</strong> Aetna and Cigna better; Bupa limited</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Regional Considerations</h3>
        <ul class="text-neutral-700 text-sm space-y-2">
          <li>• Tropical disease coverage essential</li>
          <li>• Evacuation to Singapore often included</li>
          <li>• English-speaking hospitals in capitals</li>
          <li>• Medical tourism (Thai/Malaysian) lowers costs</li>
          <li>• Visa requirements vary (Thailand Elite, MM2H)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-800 mb-3">Healthcare Quality Tiers</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">Premium (Singapore)</h4>
          <ul class="text-blue-700 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• World-class facilities</li>
            <li>• Highest costs in region</li>
            <li>• International standards</li>
            <li>• Medical tourism hub</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">High Quality (Thailand/Malaysia)</h4>
          <ul class="text-blue-700 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Excellent private hospitals</li>
            <li>• Affordable prices</li>
            <li>• Medical tourism destination</li>
            <li>• JCI-accredited options</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-800 mb-2">Developing (Vietnam/Philippines)</h4>
          <ul class="text-blue-700 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Good urban facilities</li>
            <li>• Improving rapidly</li>
            <li>• Variable outside cities</li>
            <li>• Evacuation option valuable</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="best-for" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Which Is Best For You?</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-primary-800 mb-2">Choose Cigna Global if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-primary-700 space-y-1">
          <li>• Thailand is your primary base</li>
          <li>• You travel across multiple SEA countries</li>
          <li>• Direct billing availability matters</li>
          <li>• You want the largest network</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-purple-50 border-l-4 border-purple-600 p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-purple-800 mb-2">Choose Bupa Global if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-purple-700 space-y-1">
          <li>• Singapore is your base</li>
          <li>• Premium hospital access is priority</li>
          <li>• You want VIP medical treatment</li>
          <li>• Service quality matters most</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-l-4 border-green-600 p-4">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-2">Choose Aetna International if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-green-700 space-y-1">
          <li>• Budget is a significant factor</li>
          <li>• You're in a major city</li>
          <li>• $5M coverage is sufficient</li>
          <li>• You prefer a US-based insurer</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="faqs" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">Should I include Singapore in my coverage area?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Including Singapore significantly increases premiums (30-50%) but provides access to the region's best healthcare for serious conditions. Many expats in Thailand or Malaysia include Singapore for evacuation purposes, treating it as a safety net rather than primary care location.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">Is tropical disease coverage included?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Yes, all three providers include tropical diseases (dengue, malaria, typhoid, etc.) in standard coverage. Treatment is covered like any other illness—no special riders needed. Make sure your plan includes outpatient if you want clinic treatment for minor cases.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">How does direct billing work in Thailand?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">At network hospitals, you present your insurance card at admission. The hospital contacts your insurer for pre-authorization, and bills them directly—you pay nothing (or just deductibles). Non-emergency care may require pre-approval; emergencies proceed immediately with paperwork handled later.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-2">What if I need to evacuate to Singapore?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Medical evacuation is included in all three plans. If local treatment is inadequate, your insurer will arrange transport to Singapore (or your home country) for appropriate care. This is particularly valuable when based in Vietnam, Cambodia, or rural areas of other countries.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="bg-neutral-100 rounded-lg p-6 text-sm text-neutral-600">
    <p><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Insurance pricing, networks, and coverage details change frequently. Regional healthcare quality and availability vary significantly. Always verify current coverage and networks directly with providers before purchasing. This comparison is for informational purposes only.</p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
